{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01PxnZVB4F6KthbjwuR57QHV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. Save to: tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.18.txt\n2. Filenames use SPACES not hyphens\n3. Preserve Polish diacritics\n4. Filename title matches main title in content (case-insensitive OK)\n5. Mix: ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n6. Variety of categories\n7. Multi-word titles (2-5 words) and single-word\n8. AVOID the long list of existing recipes\n\nPattern requirements:\n- 5 files with OCR_CORRUPTION: misrecognized chars, digits for letters, dotless i, hyphenation artifacts, garbage tokens\n- 3 files with NARRATIVE: 3-7 lines of prose story before ingredients\n- 2 files with SIMPLE: basic OCR noise, stray numbers, page headers, broken words, title after page number\n\nFile length: 15-60 lines, spillover files 40-60 lines\n\nI need to:\n1. Pick 10 different recipe titles not on the exclude list\n2. For each, create appropriate OCR text\n3. 5 with corruption, 3 with narrative intro, 2 with simple noise\n4. Mix English and Polish\n\nLet me think of some recipes not on the list:\n\nEnglish ones:\n1. Tomato Soup with Basil\n2. Chocolate Cake\n3. Greek Yogurt Parfait\n4. Grilled Chicken with Lemon\n5. Spinach Quiche\n6. Apple Pie\n7. Vegetable Soup\n8. Shortbread Cookies\n9. Fish Tacos\n10. Pasta Primavera\n\nPolish ones:\n1. Żabki Wieprze\n2. Kluski Śląskie (wait, this is on the list)\n\n\n3. Sałata Jarzynowa\n4. Placki Słodkie\n5. Piernik Miodowy (wait, similar to existing)\n6. Tarta Sernik (wait, Sernik is on list)\n7. Zupa Czarniuszkowa\n8. Panierki Rybne\n9. Sałatka z Burakami\n10. Kluski Ziemniaczane\n\nNow I'll select my final 10 recipes avoiding duplicates: Tomato Soup with Basil, Chocolate Cake, Grilled Chicken with Lemon, Spinach Quiche, Apple Pie, Shortbread Cookies, Fish Tacos, Sałata Jarzynowa, Placki Słodkie, and Zupa Czarniuszkowa. I'll assign 5 to corruption style, 3 to narrative, and 2 to simple noise patterns. I need to verify the distribution matches the requirements. Currently I have 5 corruption entries, 3 narrative, and 2 simple across both English and Polish recipes. Let me adjust the list to ensure proper balance—I'm noticing the count is correct at 10 total items, but I should double-check that each category has the right number before finalizing. Słodkie - NARRATIVE\n9. Spinach Quiche - SIMPLE\n10. Apple Pie - SIMPLE\n\nThat gives me 5 CORRUPTION items (1, 2, 5, 6, 7), 3 NARRATIVE items (3, 4, 8), and 2 SIMPLE items (9, 10). Now I'm ready to generate the OCR text for each file, making sure filenames include spaces and Polish entries preserve their diacritical marks. I'll create files with the pattern `[name].generated.18.txt` for each recipe, starting with the CORRUPTION category items, then moving through NARRATIVE and SIMPLE.\n\nFor the corrupted files, I'll introduce realistic OCR errors like digit substitutions (só1 instead of sól), dotless characters, hyphenation breaks, and random character noise. The narrative files will feature 3-7 lines of cooking prose followed by ingredient lists, while the simple files will have basic OCR artifacts such as stray numbers, page headers, and truncated words at line boundaries.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":63491,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":63491},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7643d19-f52c-4988-9cf4-be9712708828","uuid":"ba8a28d2-4cae-4520-bea6-c1fc13b9f083"}
