{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_014SSC1bJsN5fEsnwg3h23d9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013t24hwquYcFg1PgUcj4Suu","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Grilled Chicken with Lemon.generated.18.txt","content":"GRILLED CHICKEN WITH LEMON\n\nThis classic Mediterranean dish has graced dinner tables for generations, combining\nthe brightness of fresh lemon with tender, juicy chicken. The marinade is simple yet\ntransformative—just a few pantry staples create a depth of flavor that belies its ease\nof preparation. Whether you're entertaining guests or preparing a weeknight family dinner,\nthis dish delivers restaurant-quality results with minimal effort. The grill marks not only\nlook beautiful but also add a subtle smokiness that complements the zesty lemon perfectly.\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts (about 6 oz each)\n- 1/4 cup extra virgin olive oil\n- Zest and juice of 3 fresh lemons\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 sprigs fresh rosemary\n- 2 sprigs fresh thyme\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n\nPREPARATION:\n\nCombine olive oil, lemon zest, lemon juice, garlic, rosemary, thyme, salt, pepper,\nand red pepper flakes in a bowl. Place chicken breasts in a large ziplock bag and\npour marinade over. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, or up to overnight.\n\nPreheat grill to medium-high heat (about 400°F). Remove chicken from marinade and\ngrill for 6-7 minutes per side until internal temperature reaches 165°F.\n\nSERVES: 4\nCOOK TIME: 20 minutes\nMARINATING TIME: 2+ hours"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":512,"cache_read_input_tokens":81328,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":512},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard